sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / CI Pipeline
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Kueue Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (internal certs)
    participant JobCtrl as Kueue Job Controller
    participant Cache as Kueue Cache/Queue<br/>(in-process)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler<br/>(scheduling loop)
    participant ProvCtrl as Provisioning Controller
    participant Autoscaler as Cluster Autoscaler
    participant CloudAPI as Cloud Provider API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RemoteAPI as Remote Cluster API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MKReconciler as MultiKueue Reconciler

    Note over User,Scheduler: Flow 1: Job Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create Job/PyTorchJob/RayJob<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission webhook call<br/>Auth: API server auth
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: 3. Validate/Mutate response<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Note over Webhook: Job created in suspended state

    JobCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch job resources
    JobCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    JobCtrl->>Cache: Enqueue Workload

    Scheduler->>Cache: 4. Snapshot cache state
    Note over Scheduler: Evaluate pending workloads<br/>Assign flavors<br/>Check quotas & borrowing limits<br/>Consider preemption
    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: 5. Admit Workload<br/>(update status with admission)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    JobCtrl->>K8sAPI: 6. Unsuspend Job<br/>(set suspend=false)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Note over K8sAPI: Job pods start running

    Note over ProvCtrl,CloudAPI: Flow 3: Provisioning Request

    ProvCtrl->>K8sAPI: 1. Create ProvisioningRequest CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Autoscaler->>K8sAPI: 2. Read ProvisioningRequest<br/>Auth: Autoscaler SA
    Autoscaler->>CloudAPI: 3. Provision nodes<br/>Auth: Cloud credentials<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    CloudAPI-->>Autoscaler: Nodes provisioned
    Autoscaler->>K8sAPI: Update PR status
    ProvCtrl->>K8sAPI: 4. Sync PR status → AdmissionCheck<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Note over ProvCtrl: Admission check passes<br/>Workload can be admitted

    Note over MKReconciler,RemoteAPI: Flow 2: MultiKueue Federation

    MKReconciler->>RemoteAPI: 1. Connect to remote cluster<br/>Auth: Kubeconfig auth<br/>TLS 1.2+
    MKReconciler->>RemoteAPI: 2. Create remote Workload<br/>Auth: Kubeconfig auth
    Note over RemoteAPI: Remote Kueue admits workload
    RemoteAPI-->>MKReconciler: 3. Workload admitted remotely
    MKReconciler->>K8sAPI: 4. Sync status to local cluster<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
